{
  "texts": [
    "LptA I36pBPA was purified as described previously 59.",
    "In brief, E. coli BL21 (λDE3) cells containing pSup-BpaRS-6TRN and pET22b-LptA(I36Am) were grown to an OD 600 of around 0.6 at 37 °C in LB medium containing 50 μg ml -1 carbenicillin, 30 μg ml -1 chloramphenicol and 0.8 mM ultraviolet-irradiation-cross-linkable amino acid p-benzoyl phenylalanine (pBPA) (BaChem).",
    "Cells were then induced with 50 μM isopropyl IPTG; allowed to grow for 2 h; collected; resuspended in a mixture containing 50 mM Tris-HCl (pH 7.4), 250 mM sucrose and 3 mM EDTA; incubated on ice for 30 min; and pelleted (6,000g, 10 min).",
    "The supernatant was supplemented with 1 mM PMSF and 10 mM imidazole and pelleted (100,000g, 30 min).",
    "The supernatant was incubated with Ni-NTA resin, which was then washed twice (20 column volumes of 20 mM Tris-HCl (pH 8.0), 150 mM NaCl, 10% (v/v) glycerol and 20 mM imidazole)."
  ]
}